            "content": {
              "text": "The chapter underscores the indispensable role of the private sector in accelerating the energy transition. It explores strategies to attract private investment, such as blended finance models, public-private partnerships (PPPs), and risk mitigation mechanisms. The chapter discusses common barriers to private sector engagement, including political instability, regulatory uncertainty, and high upfront costs. It also highlights tools like guarantees, insurance products, and concessional finance to reduce investment risks and improve the bankability of renewable energy projects."
